1.title: The Birth of Santino
1.plot: Found abounded as an infant in a cemetery, Santino is adopted by a group of priests in a small town, who all pitch in to raise him as a little boy. Santino grows up happily in the church living with the priests, who raise him as their own. He proves to be a handful, so the priests all decide to scold the little boy. But they accidentally overhear him praying to God about being thankful for all the love the priests have shown him. This softens Father Anthony's heart and he relents on punishing the boy. But one day, a parishioner says some harsh words to Santino, which ...

But Father Anthony refuses to give up the land. Meanwhile, word starts to spread around town that it was Santino who miraculously healed Joy. The next day, Enrique finds out that his son Rico was hurt by Cocoy. The mayor orders the police to arrest Cocoy and take him to jail.

The priests are concerned about the boy's safety now that almost everyone is after him. On the other hand, Enrique worries that he may never get the chance to close down the monastery now that the priests have the whole town on their side. Santino begins to heal the sick, and in return, he tells them to do good unto others. But during one healing session, Santino faints after helping a sick person.

Now that Santino is gone, Enrique will have more power in driving out the priests and closing down the monastery.

Kate later tells Ricardo that Michael is his son. However, she forbids him from telling their son the truth. The next day, Ricardo decides to leave the carnival and starts a new life some place else. Santino tells Kate about Ricardo, and at the church, she catches up on him. Kate and Ricardo reconcile, and Michael finally meets his real father.

48.title: Chesca Begins Looking for Her Mother from an Indecent Place
48.plot: Cheska works at the beer house to save up money so she can search for her birth mother in Bagong Pag-asa. Cheska believes that her mother, Ellen, once worked in the said beer house. She meets Tilde and Marj, the matron of the beer house. But Marj tells Cheska that she doesn't know anyone named Ellen. The truth is Marj is the real mother of Cheska. Marj goes to Cheska's surrogate parents and tells them about the young lady's whereabouts in exchange of money.

49.title: Chesca's Devastated Upon Knowing Her Real Mother
49.plot: In the middle of her sexy performance on stage, Chesca was finally found by her surrogate parents after Marj led them to they work. There, it was revealed to her that Marj was indeed Ellen-the birth mother that she has been looking for all these years. Upon hearing the news, she was pretty much enraged. She took off as fast as she could and went straight to the monastery where Father Anthony took her in for the night. The following morning, Chesca finally decided to meet with her parents who have been waiting all night outside the monastery for her. After speaking ...

50.title: Margie Confesses to Santino That She Truly Loves Her Daughter, Chesca
50.plot: Mario drops by the Mayor's office to confront Enrique regarding his ill treatment towards Stella. But instead of realizing his own fault, Enrique grows more furious about the matter, putting all the blame to her poor daughter. With a lot of things confusing Stella at the moment, including her growing problem with her sick mother, she finally decides to break up with Cocoy so that she could focus on setting things straight with her family. Upon hearing of the news, Santino decides to visit Stella. And on the said visit, Santino sneaks in Malena's room with hopes that ...

51.title: Cocoy and Stella Plan to Elope
51.plot: Enrique catches Stella and Cocoy hiding inside her room. When Malena hears of this news, she immediately decides to separate the two lovers for good by sending her daughter to America. Stella is left helpless. Not wanting to be sent away from the love of her life, she discreetly slips in a letter to Cocoy asking him to elope. Unfortunately, as wished by Malena who had heard of their plan, Cocoy gets arrested by the police before he even reaches their meeting place. Thinking that Cocoy may have abandoned her, Stella went back home and submit herself to her mother's ...

52.title: Cocoy Is Released from Prison
52.plot: A well-loved grade three teacher from Santino's school is informed of her upcoming discharge due to the institution's cutback. Only a year away from her retirement, Ms. Antazo has been considered as one of the possible candidates for dismissal. Due to her intense passion for teaching and great love for her students, the old maiden tries to appeal to those in power. Unfortunately, the authorities are more concerned with the institution's income rather than its principles, thus their decision remains unmoved. How can Santino possibly make a change in the life of another...

53.title: Ms. Antazo Regrets Putting All Her Life Into Teaching
53.plot: Santino bumps into Ms. Nieves Antazo at the cemetery as she silently pays respect to her parents' grave. She breaks down into tears upon realizing that she might have made the wrong choice in life, just as her parents suspected during her early years. She looks back at everything she gave up just to pursue her teaching career, and she couldn't help but feel a strike of regret now that she lost the very reason why she is alive. On the other hand, Enrique's devious plan to regain possession of the golden image of Sto. Nino for his personal interest falls into place as ...

54.title: Enrique Exploits the Golden Sto. Niño
54.plot: The priests in the monastery discover that the municipal government is collecting donations from the devotees of the golden Sto. Niño that now peacefully dwells in their town hall. Thinking that Enrique may be using it for such an ill cause, the priests drop by the said office to find out for themselves. To their surprise, they discover that the Mayor uses the said proceeds to feed the needy; little do they know, the said plot is part of the incumbent Mayor, who is hoping for a re-election, to prepare his own image for the upcoming election; as planned by no other ...

55.title: Tilde Gets an Unexpected Visitor
55.plot: Malena and Enrique's act fooled the whole town, including the priests in the monastery, into believing that the golden Sto. Niño is indeed miraculous. Realizing that Malena's wit could gain him another term in office, Enrique decides to finally let go of Tilde and knit things up with his wife. Aside from the unexpected break-up, another surprise comes to Tilde's attention. The girl who consistently calls her for questioning regarding the disappearance of a certain girl named Teresa suddenly appears before her. Quite worried that her name will be incorporated on the ...

56.title: Janet Finally Finds Teresa
56.plot: After seeking the help of Mario, Tilde finally admits to Janet that the girl she has been looking for, Teresa, is already dead. Together with this revelation, Tilde also shares to the new comer the real reason why Teresa went to Bagong Pag-asa in the first place; to collect the money she owed her. She says that she kept this truth in silence for a very long time because she feared that the police might see this as a motive for murder. Upon hearing of the said revelation, Janet suddenly breaks down. Now that she had confirmed that her best friend is already dead, her ...

57.title: Janet Meets Santino
57.plot: As Janet lays her eyes on Santino, she couldn't help but see his resemblance to her deceased friend, Teresa. If she has no idea that Teresa's son, Gabriel, might be staying with her former landlord somewhere in Manila, she might have thought that Santino is indeed the kid she is looking for. Upon his return to the monastery, Santino immediately informs the priests of his new found friend, taking them by surprise. They used to think that Teresa is Santino's mother, but after Father Anthony received a confirmation that she isn't, he insists to keep the said detail from ...

58.title: Mario's Nephew Pays Him a Visit
58.plot: After an unexpected visit from his nephew he hadn't seen for such a long time, it is revealed that Mario happens to have a half-sister, who used to be a former sexy star, named Adel San Jose. At the peek of the former actress' career, she unexpectedly got pregnant. The said pregnancy conceived Boy George, which she claims to be the cause of the downfall of her then blooming career. Since Boy George could remember, his mother continuously blames him for all the misfortunes happening in her life; giving her all the reasons to purposely maltreat him. But despite all the ...

59.title: Boy George Runs Away
59.plot: Fed up with the almost unending torture, Boy George decides to pack all his things up and head out the door, leaving his mother behind, alone. With no other place to go, he goes straight to his Uncle Mario's home, wherein he also discloses the maltreatment his mother does to him. After hearing the said revelation, Mario confronts his sister who, unfortunately, falls short on listening to his argument. Upon Boy George's decision to return home, Adela welcomes him with a cold treatment. On the other end, people in Bagong Pag-asa are starting to doubt whether or not the ...

60.title: Santino Extends His Hand to Adela
60.plot: Even behind bars, Adela continues to maltreat his son Boy George. As Santino stands witness to the said ill treatment, he couldn't help but show concern towards his new friend. Santino tries to enlighten Adela but she refuses to hear him out as she stands firm with her belief that all the mishaps in her life is caused by Boy George's conception. Completely fed up with his mother's rants, Boy George runs away from home again; but this time, he is very much decided that it will be for good. After her release from prison, Adela is not surprised that she has to go in an ...

61.title: Adela and Boy George Reconcile
61.plot: With no one else to turn to, Adela decides take into consideration Santino's offer. He openly discloses to her how much her son Boy George truly loves her. With the help of his words, Adela gradually realizes all the mistakes she had done towards her kid. After the said realization, she immediately decides to get in touch with him so she could pay him all the necessary apologies. Unfortunately, Boy George is put behind bars after assaulting a man who unknowingly bad-mouthed his mother. Concerned of her son's stature, Adela rushes to the police station. Upon sight of ...

62.title: Malena Outsmarts Enrique
62.plot: While Enrique whines all over the place after being double crossed by the men he hired to steal the golden image of the Santo Niño, Malena silently celebrates her victory. Aside from taking pleasure from Enrique's failure without her help, she is also pleased by the overwhelming amount deposited in her account in exchange of the real golden image of the Santo Niño, which she discreetly took from Enrique after replacing it with a phony image. Unfortunately, her pleasure will not be standing for too long because Enrique finally discovers her devious plot; and upon ...

63.title: Enrique Tries to Get Back at Malena
63.plot: In order to get back at Malena, Enrique hires a group of armed men. The plan is simple: the men are to enter their home and hold Malena hostage; after Malena signs the withdrawal slip, they are to immediately leave. Unfortunately, the plan goes out of hand after one of the housemaids they hold captive found a way to escape and tip the authorities. Immediately, the house is surrounded by the police, ready to attack. And when they are about to barge in the crime scene, Enrique immediately stops them by suggesting that he will try to negotiate with them instead. Inside ...

64.title: Enrique's Men Lose His Money
64.plot: Enrique successfully withdraws the money from his wife Malena's account. After he hands over the bag of cash to the hired thieves, Selda and Mario suddenly comes out to chase the culprits. On the said pursuit, the gangsters decide to hide the bag in a parked truck before searching for cover. Instantly, Selda and Mario lose sight of them; but unfortunately, after the two police have left, the culprits realize that the truck is already gone, bringing with it their boss Enrique's money. On the other hand, Carla tries to talk with her older sister regarding the growing ...

65.title: Carla's Little Secret Is Revealed
65.plot: After hearing of the truth regarding the possibility that his mother is still alive, Santino grows a little depressed. He spends the whole day in the cemetery meddling on the thought about his mother. On his way back to the monastery, he sees Carla again, crying. Concerned of the young lady, he immediately approaches her to ask her what is wrong. With no one else to talk to, Carla decides to admit her problem to Santino. She tells him she is pregnant and she doesn't know how to tell it to his father who sees her as his perfect little daughter. Carla asks for her older...

66.title: Carla Runs Away with Judith and Their Mother
66.plot: After Manolo Sandoval realizes that the whole town is gossiping about his daughter's untimely pregnancy, he decides to lock Carla up in the house. And in order to avoid tainting his very much preserved name, he also ends up suggesting abortion to his precious little daughter. Carla's older sister, Judith, overhears his father's mischievous plan so she decides to help Carla escape. On their way out, their mother catches them; but instead of stopping them, she decides to go along with them. With nowhere else to go, Carla leads them to the monastery where Father Anthony ...

67.title: Manolo Is Finally Enlightened
67.plot: Manolo hears of his daughter's plan to go in a shelter for single mothers. Upon hearing this, he finally decides to get her back before he loses her for good. He pays the needed apology for his actions, which Carla heartily accepts. After realizing, too, that he has been an inadequate father towards Judith, he also confronts her to ask for her forgiveness. In tears, Judith is moved by his father's enlightenment; and for the very first time, she feels she is part of their family once again. On the other end, a lonely couple ends up probing the small town of Bagong ...

68.title: The Lonely Couple Is Persistent to Find Their Long Lost Child
68.plot: Gary and Miriam's kid has been lost for years, but they have never given up on looking for him. With the help of Selda and Mario, their search is made easier. The two police keep on showing them pictures of reported missing children surrendered in orphanages around town; but she confirms that none of the said children is her son. To his dismay, Gary decides to finally give up on the search; so he tells his wife that if the next child that Selda and Mario will be introducing to them is not their son, then they will finally submit themselves to the truth that they will ...

69.title: Father Jose Gets Emotional
69.plot: Though disheartened, the priests in the monastery are willing to submit Santino to Miriam and Gary once they prove that they are the real parents of the wonder kid. Though the blood ties between the Santino and the couple are not yet confirmed, the bond between the two parties are indeed undeniable. The two parties compliment each other very well, raising an uneasy feeling of jealousy on the part of Father Jose, the closest priest to Santino. Knowing that his fatherhood to Santino is nearing its end upon the return of his real parents, he couldn't help but burst into ...

70.title: Santino Goes Home with Gary and Miriam
70.plot: Gary notices how Santino brightens up the day of his wife, so he decides to ask the priests in the monastery to let the child go home with them while waiting for the DNA test results. Father Anthony doesn't approve of the said suggestion, but he instantly gives in to the request after Santino himself approves of Gary's suggestion. Among all the priests, Father Jose is the one most affected of Santino's decision; but despite his personal interests, he admits to Santino that he is truly happy that he had found the family he has been looking for all those years. On the ...

71.title: Gary and Miriam Discover That Santino Is Not Their Son
71.plot: The DNA test result that Gary brought home reveals that Santino is in fact their missing son. The couple immediately informs the priests in the monastery about this, together with their plans of bringing Santino back to Manila with them. As a final request, Father Anthony asks the couple if they could lend them the child before they leave the town for good. The two willingly agrees. Along the way, it is revealed that the result of Santino's DNA test result is counterfeited, by no other than Malena; but unfortunately for her, Mario and Selda immediately discovers the ...

72.title: Miriam Breaks the Painful News to Santino
72.plot: After receiving a confirmation from the DNA testing center that Santino isn't really the son that Gary and Miriam is looking for, the latter is left with no choice but to break the news to the poor child. Upon hearing the painful news, Santino instantly bursts into tears. With too much pain in his heart, he immediately runs into Bro's embrace. Bro selflessly consoles Santino's burdened heart, giving him enough courage to go back in the monastery and face his surrogate mother. Finally, he decides to let go of her despite his intense longing for a motherly love. To the ...

73.title: Abby Bumps Into Santino
73.plot: Enrique discovers the news regarding Santino's unsuccessful departure from Bagong Pag-asa. Dismayed of the unexpected news, he practically goes furious, putting all the blame on his wife Malena and her poor planning. On the other hand, Santino is still not over the pain of his disappointment. Still in search for a motherly care, he ends up missing as he obliviously walks through the streets of their town with high hopes that his instincts will bring him closer to his mother. Upon realizing Santino is gone, the priests in the monastery immediately go in search for him,...

74.title: Abby Turns Down Her Grandfather's Offer
74.plot: After realizing that Santino is indeed lost, Abby takes the initiative to guide him back to the monastery. Despite his return, Father Jose can not hide his dismay regarding Santino's irrational acts, so he decides to confront him regarding his shortcoming. On the other hand, Abby too is scolded by her grandfather, Carlos, after she decides to turn down his offer. Carlos wishes Abby to takeover their tocino business, but she refuses; she suggests selling the business instead, an idea which further enrages Carlos. imdb.plot outline: When he was just a baby, Santino was abandoned by his mother in a monastery. Santino was raised by the caring priests Father Anthony, Father Jose, and Father Ringo. As a young boy, Santino will find a friend in a mysterious person which he calls "Bro" (shortened for brother) who will help him change the lives of the people in their town. May Bukas Pa is a story that is set to open the eyes of viewers that there will always be hope amidst trials and difficulties. Miracles don't just fall from heaven but comes to those who keep their faith.
